  "text": "Invalid input for calculator: {'answer': \"The relative improvement percentage from an error rate of 12% to 7.5% is calculated as follows: \\n\\nRelative Improvement = ((12 - 7.5) / 12) * 100 = (4.5 / 12) * 100 = 37.5%. \\n\\nThis means there is a 37.5% improvement in the error rate. \\n\\nNow, regarding the research papers, I didn't specifically check for mentions of ethical or regulatory challenges in the initial findings. Let me search for that explicitly.\"}"
